## Implementation Sequence

### Phase 1: MVP Foundation
1. Update existing Xcode project with SwiftUI lifecycle
2. Set up or update scalable directory structure
3. Implement core models and services
4. Configure basic UI theme and components
5. Create initial README and architecture documentation

### Phase 2: Core Functionality
1. Implement HealthKitManager for permissions and data access
2. Create HealthDataService for processing health data
3. Design and implement health metric models
4. Add HealthKit permissions in Info.plist
5. Design frictionless questionnaire flow
6. Document HealthKit integration approach

### Phase 3: Impact and Projection Calculation
1. Implement LifeImpactModel with scientific algorithms
2. Create LifeImpactService for coordinating calculations
3. Implement LifeProjectionService for long-term projections
4. Design impact data structures and persistence
5. Connect health data flow to impact calculations
6. Integrate questionnaire data with calculations
7. Document scientific basis and algorithm implementation

### Phase 4: UI Implementation
1. Build revised onboarding flow with "little yesses" approach
2. Implement questionnaire flow (5-8 questions)
3. Create payment screen with subscription options
4. Implement dashboard with dual battery visualization
5. Create metric cards showing different power levels
6. Add charts and data visualization
7. Implement privacy-respecting analytics
8. Document UI components and user flows

### Phase 5: MVP Refinement
1. Add simple battery charging/discharging animations
2. Implement basic settings
3. Optimize performance for scale
4. Add accessibility features
5. Polish essential UI elements
6. Test and optimize conversion funnel
7. Complete user-facing documentation
8. Finalize developer documentation